---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { temples, alwars, regions, songs } from "../data";
const verses = songs.reduce((n, s) => n + s.blocks.filter((b) => b.type === "verse").length, 0);
---

<Base title="About this project" description="About the bilingual 108 Divya Desam guide and how it was made.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> › About</p>
    <h1>About this guide</h1>
    <div style="max-width:46rem;">
      <p>
        The <strong>108 Divya Desam</strong> are the sacred abodes of Sriman Narayana (Vishnu)
        celebrated in the <em>Naalayira Divya Prabandham</em> — the 4,000 Tamil verses composed by
        the twelve Alwar saints between roughly the 6th and 9th centuries CE. For centuries this
        treasure has lived primarily in Tamil. This guide aims to open it to readers everywhere.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every name, place, and verse is shown in the original Tamil alongside an English
        rendering — a Roman transliteration so the sounds can be read and chanted, and an English
        meaning so the sense can be understood.
      </p>

      <h2>What's here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>{temples.length}</strong> Divya Desam temples across <strong>{regions.length}</strong> regions</li>
        <li>The <strong>{alwars.length}</strong> Alwar saints, their birthplaces, and the temples they sang</li>
        <li><strong>{verses.toLocaleString()}</strong> verses from the Divya Prabandham and Mangalasasanam</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>A note on the translations</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Temple, place, and Alwar names and the menu structure are verified. The English
        transliterations and verse meanings are machine-assisted first drafts produced with
        scholarly care but still under review — items not yet rendered into English are marked
        <span class="draft">(draft)</span>. The Tamil source is always preserved as the authority.
        Corrections from devotees and scholars are warmly welcomed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
